commit 977c867714ee93c16126f5a63d1e341aec360091
Author: Anton Dvornikov <prilive.company@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri May 8 14:57:16 2026 +0000

    fix: parasitoid trial-feedback (3 real bugs + 1 doc gap + 1 missing template)
    
    Developer running v1.6.0 against parasitoid trial reported 4 issues.
    3 are real bugs, 1 is a missing template. Fixed all four. Plus a
    governance-rule addition the developer correctly identified.
    
    (1) require-second-opinion.sh: cat ... 2>/dev/null false-positive
    
    The mutating-Bash detector at line 160 used regex
      cat[[:space:]]+[^|<]*>+[[:space:]]*[^&[:space:]]
    to catch `cat > file` (writing files via Bash to bypass Edit/Write
    hooks). The regex matched `cat foo 2>/dev/null` too — the `>+` part
    caught the `>` of `2>` even though numbered fd redirects are read-only.
    
    Trace: for `cat foo 2>/dev/null`:
      - cat[[:space:]]+ matches "cat "
      - [^|<]* greedy then backtracks to "foo 2"
      - >+ matches ">"
      - [[:space:]]* matches empty
      - [^&[:space:]] matches "/" → false-positive deny
    
    Fix: change `[^|<]*>+` to `([^|<]*[^|<0-9])?>+`. The character
    immediately before `>+` must NOT be a digit. Excludes 1>, 2>, 9>
    while still catching `cat > file` (space before >) and `cat foo > bar`
    (space before >). Reported by the parasitoid trial; smoke test added.
    
    (2) detect-ai-bloat.sh: false-positive on markdown TODO discussion
    
    The TODO/FIXME/HACK scan ran against ALL changed files (`git diff` with
    no path filter). Markdown spec/red-proof/adjudication files often
    discuss TODOs as text — every commit adding such discussion tripped
    the advisory hook with no Go code in the diff.
    
    Fix: restrict TODO scan to *.go (matching the existing exported-symbols
    scan's filter). Smoke test verifies markdown-only TODO edits emit no
    advisory; .go TODO edits still fire correctly.
    
    (3) green-proof.md template (was missing)
    
    The v1.6.0 commit-time gate (gate-tier1-commit.sh) requires
    .tdd/green-proof.md but the v1.6.0 ship didn't include a template for
    it. Operators were expected to mirror red-proof.md by hand.
    
    Fix: add .tdd/templates/green-proof.md with the same shape as
    red-proof.md but with PASS-oriented sections:
      - Command run (same as red, ideally with -race -count=1)
      - Output verbatim (PASS for tests that were RED)
      - What this green proves
      - Why this is not a fake green (no skipped tests, no test mods, no
        -short flag, race detector green, count=1)
      - Coverage delta (optional)
      - Reviewer confirmation
    
    (4) Forbidden rule: never modify hook scripts mid-cycle
    
    The developer hit a v1.3.1 chicken-and-egg deadlock and patched
    require-second-opinion.sh in-place to honor the
    allow_test_file_edits_without_gate config flag. Their patch was
    reasonable in spirit (they correctly identified an actual bug in the
    hook ignoring a configured flag) but wrong in scope: agent-applied
    governance modification mid-cycle without consulting the upstream
    maintainer.
    
    The developer self-flagged this in their feedback. The right escape
    hatch is documented in v1.6.0 (operator authorizes config flag with
    reason in commit), but the rule wasn't explicit. Now it is.
    
    New "Forbidden" rule in go-tdd.md:
      - Never modify hook scripts mid-cycle to unblock yourself.
      - If a gate creates a logical deadlock you cannot resolve via
        documented flows (return-to-red, killswitch env vars, config
        flag overrides), STOP and surface it.
      - Hook scripts are governance infrastructure; patching them
        mid-cycle is unauthorized modification of the project's safety
        controls.
      - Lists the legitimate escape hatches: operator config-flag flip,
        killswitch env var, upstream gate-design fix.
    
    The v1.6.0 phase-aware test policy makes the original chicken-and-egg
    unrepresentable, so this rule is preventative for future deadlocks
    the design hasn't anticipated.
    
    WHAT IS NOT FIXED IN THIS COMMIT:
    
    - Tier detection bug in /second-opinion plan-mode (B4 from developer
      feedback): the script greps tier1_path_regexes against plan text but
      `\.go$` end-of-line anchor doesn't match paths embedded in prose.
      Workaround: v1.6.0 already defaults non-Tier-1 to gpt-5.5 too
      (second_opinion.model_default), making the bug cosmetic. Real fix
      deferred unless operators report value.
    
    - Per-cycle Pass A opt-out (C3): killswitch is per-shell. Workaround:
      prepend env var to single invocation. Marker-file pattern deferred
      unless operators report value.
    
    - Eval harness for Pass A (mentioned in spec §8): not built. Pass A
      validation remains "flip flag on next Tier 1 cycle and observe."
    
    SMOKE TESTS: 81 → 86 (+5 new):
      - cat ... 2>/dev/null no longer false-positive as mutating Bash
      - cat foo 1>/dev/null no longer false-positive
      - cat > file (genuine mutating) still denied without adjudication
      - AI-bloat hook silent on markdown-only TODO edit (no advisory)
      - AI-bloat hook still fires on .go TODO + new exported symbol

