commit 5968f53158254a64525c3b7e6598d193a957b8eb
Author: Anton Dvornikov <prilive.company@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri May 1 22:43:47 2026 +0000

    feature: /second-opinion skill — manual cross-model review via Codex CLI (Path B+, experimental)
    
    Adds an OPTIONAL skill that invokes OpenAI Codex CLI as a read-only
    external reviewer before non-trivial Tier 1 implementation work.
    
    Workflow when invoked:
      1. Resolve target (.tdd/current-plan.md / git diff HEAD / file / question)
      2. Apply minimal redaction
      3. codex exec --sandbox read-only --ephemeral with anti-sycophancy prompt
      4. Parse JSON findings, decide accept/partial/pushback per finding
      5. Surface to user with rationale; do not silently edit code
    
    Files:
      - .claude/skills/second-opinion/SKILL.md    (the skill)
      - scripts/doctor.sh                          (optional codex check + auth status)
      - CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md                      (one-line entry under Skills available)
      - MAINTAINING.md                             ('Second-opinion skill design choices')
    
    Design choices (see MAINTAINING.md for full rationale):
      - Manual / skill-description-driven invocation; NO auto-fire hooks.
        Auto-fire was rejected pre-shipping because it forces cost on every
        Tier 1 ceremony regardless of whether the review would add value.
      - Single-pass; no Round 2 debate. Re-invoke with refined input if needed.
      - Codex is OPTIONAL. make doctor reports it but does not require it.
        Failures (codex missing, not logged in, timeout) are silent and
        non-blocking — the skill exits 0 with a one-line note.
      - Default model: gpt-5.5 (newest frontier). Override with
        SECOND_OPINION_MODEL. SECOND_OPINION_DISABLE=1 silences the skill.
      - No config file, no JSON schema, no eval harness. Two env vars total.
      - Anti-deference framing both in the prompt (be skeptical, downgrade
        severities, zero findings is acceptable) and in Claude's
        decision-tree (do not change code solely because the reviewer said
        so; the reason is the underlying technical claim).
    
    Branch policy: this commit is on feature/second-opinion. Do NOT merge
    to main until 2-4 weeks of real-world use confirms the skill adds
    value. main stays at v1.3.1 as the stable team starter.
    
    Smoke tests: still 26/26 passing. The skill itself is not in the
    smoke-test set yet — testing it requires an authenticated codex
    session, which the smoke harness does not assume.
